{
  "texts": [
    "The theoretical basis of RL is the MDP, which usually consists of the agent, environment, policy function, state space, action space, reward, state transition function, and discount factor [197].",
    "The goal of the agent is to obtain an optimal policy for maximizing the cumulative discount reward by interacting with the environment.",
    "Specifically, at the ℓth time step, the agent observes the state s ℓ and takes the action a ℓ from the action space according to the policy function π(a ℓ |s ℓ), which is a conditional probability density function with respect to s ℓ and a ℓ.",
    "Then the environment transforms the state from s ℓ to s ℓ+1 according to the state transition function P (s ℓ+1 |a ℓ, s ℓ) and calculates the instant reward r ℓ = r(s ℓ, a ℓ, s ℓ+1).",
    "The 4-tuple (s ℓ, a ℓ, r ℓ, s ℓ+1) is stored in the replay buffer for training the agent via the temporal difference method, bypassing the need for manual labels."
  ]
}